title: Farha (2021)
name: Farha (2021)

trailer.name: Official Trailer
trailer.description: Farha (2021) In 1948 Palestine, 14-year-old Farha dreams of pursuing an education beyond her village. Just as her father agrees to let her delay marriage and attend a city school, their peaceful life shatters. Israeli forces arrive, displacing villagers and forcing Farha's family to flee. To protect Farha, her father hides her in a small, concealed pantry within their home. Trapped in darkness, she listens to the escalating violence outside, relying on scraps of information from the occasional visitor. Days turn into weeks as Farha grapples with fear, loneliness, and the uncertainty of her future. Through the sounds and smells filtering through the pantry door, Farha witnesses the destruction of her village and the trauma inflicted on her community. This confined perspective becomes a powerful lens through which the film portrays the devastating impact of the Nakba on ordinary lives. Farha is a poignant coming-of-age story that delves into themes of resilience, hope, and the enduring power of memory in the face of displacement and loss.

title: The Attack (2012)
name: The Attack (2012)

trailer.name: Official Trailer
trailer.description: The Attack (2012), originally titled L'Attentat in French, is a gripping political thriller drama that delves into the complex and sensitive realities of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. Based on Yasmina Khadra's novel of the same name, the film is directed by Ziad Doueiri and stars Ali Suliman as the protagonist, Dr. Amin Jaafari. The narrative unfolds in Tel Aviv, where Dr. Amin Jaafari, a successful Arab-Israeli surgeon, enjoys a seemingly perfect life with a thriving career and a loving marriage to Siham. However, tragedy strikes when Siham dies in a suicide bombing, and shockingly, she is suspected of being the bomber. Refusing to accept the accusations against his wife, Amin embarks on a personal quest to uncover the truth. The film skillfully weaves a suspenseful thriller with a profound exploration of identity, betrayal, and the profound human cost of political violence. Amin's investigation takes him on a dangerous journey into the heart of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, where he confronts uncomfortable truths about Siham, their relationship, and the broader political realities shaping their lives.

trailer.name: Official Trailer
trailer.description: The Rundown (2003), also known as Welcome to the Jungle in some territories. A classic action-comedy film starring Dwayne The Rock Johnson as Beck, a bounty hunter tasked with retrieving the wayward son of a powerful Chicago mob boss from the Amazon rainforest. The film follows Beck as he navigates the treacherous jungle, dealing with rival treasure hunters, indigenous tribes, and the bumbling incompetence of his quarry, Travis (Seann William Scott). Along the way, he also teams up with Mariana (Rosario Dawson), a tough-as-nails rainforest guide with a mysterious past. The Rundown is packed with action, laughs, and a healthy dose of Dwayne Johnson's charisma. It's a fun and entertaining film that's sure to please fans of the genre. There's a great mix of hand-to-hand combat, gunfights, and chases, all set against the stunning backdrop of the Amazon rainforest. The chemistry between Dwayne Johnson and Seann William Scott is hilarious. Their contrasting personalities make for some great comedic moments.The film is full of heart. Despite all the action and humor, The Rundown has a surprisingly sweet message about friendship and redemption.
